{
  "texts": [
    "Pd-Ros must be able to convince a citizen that goal G1 is satisfied.To reliably offer proofs of compliance, Pd-Ros assumes the presence of trusted hardware on the drone.",
    "This hardware must be capable of performing basic cryptographic operations, offer the ability to securely store an audit trail, and respond to citizen requests with a digitally-signed audit trail.",
    "Trusted hardware is typically endowed with a public/private key pair with the private key stored securely in the hardware, and the public key digitally certified by a certificate authority.",
    "This public key serves as the drone's identifier.In our prototype, we use the ARM TrustZone [10], which provides these features.",
    "3 An ARM TrustZone processor can be in one of two worlds of execution at any given instant-a secure world or a normal world."
  ]
}